{"msg_id":"8ac298fd-4167-4034-bdfb-ea38f6c3a9f5","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775663834730706593,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-ff8","priority":"p2","title":"rd join: multi-root beacon resolution and failover on name-resolution failure","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"821db9a6-de71-40d0-9e64-a9c9a1d8ea3b","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775663853527392346,"operation":"work:update","payload":{"context":"Follow-up from ready-9df. Design ref: federation-auth-naming-v2.md line 460. TOFU pinning is done (applyBeaconRootTOFU in join.go). Remaining: (1) when rd join resolves a name via beacon, try multiple roots if the first fails. (2) On name-resolution failure, surface clear error with retry guidance. Currently join.go loads a single operator root (line 315). Needs: try configured roots in order, failover to next on timeout/error.\n\n## Done condition\nrd join with a name that requires beacon resolution tries all configured roots in order. If the first root times out or errors, the next root is tried. If all roots fail, a clear error message lists which roots were tried and suggests --confirm to override TOFU pin.\n\n## File paths\n- cmd/rd/join.go — resolveName, applyBeaconRootTOFU\n- pkg/rdconfig/config.go — BeaconRoot (may need BeaconRoots plural)\n\n## Agent type: implementer\n## Model tier: sonnet\n## Test-depth: feature","target":"8ac298fd-4167-4034-bdfb-ea38f6c3a9f5"},"tags":["work:update"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"c6a56d72-4160-433d-a6fb-912a90ea26b6","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775663870017601117,"operation":"work:update","payload":{"context":"## Goal\nE2e smoke test proving rd commands work when the user's identity lives at the legacy ~/.campfire/ path (pre-0.16 migration).\n\n## Done condition\nAn e2e test that:\n1. Creates a temporary CF_HOME at a path ending in .campfire/ (simulating legacy layout)\n2. Runs cf init in that home to create an identity\n3. Runs rd init --name testproject with CF_HOME pointing to the legacy path\n4. Creates an item, lists items, shows item — all succeed\n5. Verifies no errors about missing identity or wrong path\n\n## File paths\n- test/e2e/ — new test or extend existing e2e tests\n- cmd/rd/root.go — identity resolution (verify it handles legacy path)\n\n## Veracity constraint\nMust use real cf init and real rd commands, not mocks.\n\n## Agent type: implementer\n## Model tier: haiku\n## Test-depth: test-only","target":"922df840-25f5-4fac-a465-691ff0b5cfd7"},"tags":["work:update"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"72d96d5f-2df7-407b-9e92-3838340d42ea","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775663876842700200,"operation":"work:update","payload":{"context":"## Goal\nE2e smoke test proving rd commands work on a fresh install where identity is at ~/.cf/ (the new default path, post-0.16).\n\n## Done condition\nAn e2e test that:\n1. Creates a temporary CF_HOME at a path ending in .cf/ (simulating new-install default)\n2. Runs cf init in that home to create an identity\n3. Runs rd init --name testproject with CF_HOME pointing to the new path\n4. Creates an item, lists items, shows item — all succeed\n5. Verifies no errors about missing identity or wrong path\n6. Verifies .campfire/ directory is NOT required or created\n\n## File paths\n- test/e2e/ — new test or extend existing e2e tests\n- cmd/rd/root.go — identity resolution (verify it handles new default)\n\n## Veracity constraint\nMust use real cf init and real rd commands, not mocks.\n\n## Agent type: implementer\n## Model tier: haiku\n## Test-depth: test-only","target":"f2dfbd59-6121-4749-be0a-87c005843da3"},"tags":["work:update"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"0bc0e4ba-7026-46a8-852a-442beba0b28d","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775663888872298640,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-ea6","priority":"p0","title":"ready v0.8 cleanup: e2e smoke tests, Wave 4 reviews, sweeps, face card cascade","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"50f1450e-75b6-45c3-b2c7-e31b5d5b4fa0","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775663903735349450,"operation":"work:update","payload":{"context":"Parent dispatch item for the remaining ready v0.8 work. Design campfire: 36284e31fe77a3ecea91162d7c8826adc74b7dd1296f89ae69db68fab48a71cc.\n\n## Dispatch plan\n\n### Wave 1 (parallel, no deps):\n- ready-589 (e2e: legacy ~/.campfire path, haiku)\n- ready-6ee (e2e: new ~/.cf path, haiku)\n- ready-84a (veracity: inbox watcher test double, haiku)\n- ready-aff (review code: Wave 4, haiku)\n- ready-ef4 (review test: Wave 4, haiku)\n- ready-24b (review security: Wave 4, sonnet)\n- ready-48d (review spec-compliance: Wave 4, haiku)\n\n### After Wave 1:\n- Close face card chain: ready-f00 → ready-97b → ready-22f → ready-478 → ready-b0a (all empty tracking items, cascade-close once 589+6ee done)\n- That unlocks 6 sweeps: ready-802, ready-d1a, ready-efe, ready-ebe, ready-18f, ready-852\n\n### Wave 2 (after face cards closed):\n- 6 sweeps (security, bugs, deadcode, antipatterns, testcoverage, harness)\n\n### Wave 3 (after sweeps):\n- ready-6d0 (E2E verification — blocked by all sweeps)\n- Any fix items created by sweeps/reviews\n\n### Completion:\n- Close ready-ea6\n- Close ready-665 if all blockers resolved\n\n## Strategy: shared","target":"0bc0e4ba-7026-46a8-852a-442beba0b28d"},"tags":["work:update"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
