{"msg_id":"aeb21743-e258-413f-8ba4-ef6ce3e7dec7","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775664554252473522,"operation":"work:claim","payload":{"target":"68811c47-c37e-42c5-af96-5986a9babc46"},"tags":["work:claim"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"110eead8-8928-4609-9f62-07039f16449c","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775664703119286720,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"context":"In cmd/rd/join.go, the beacon root is pinned to config (rdconfig.Save) BEFORE client.Join() is called. If the join fails (wrong campfire ID, transport error), the beacon root is permanently pinned to an untrusted value. The user must then explicitly run 'rd join --reset-beacon-root' to recover. Fix: move TOFU pin save to AFTER a successful join, or roll back on join failure. Severity: major.","for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-f43","parent_id":"ready-24b","priority":"p2","title":"fix: TOFU beacon root pinned before join succeeds — spurious pin on failed join","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"9ed5aaf7-d831-4855-b287-d3c4d622133e","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775664708925522483,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"context":"In cmd/rd/join.go, when stdin is not a terminal (CI pipelines, agent invocations), the TOFU first-use guard auto-pins any supplied --root value without user confirmation. A script that invokes 'rd join --root \u003cattacker-controlled-id\u003e' will silently pin a malicious beacon root. Subsequent joins using the correct root require --confirm or --reset-beacon-root to recover. Fix options: (1) require explicit --confirm flag even in non-interactive mode for first TOFU pin, (2) refuse to auto-pin in non-interactive mode and exit with a clear error, (3) document clearly that --confirm is required in CI. Severity: major — the whole point of TOFU is to surface first-use so users can verify the root.","for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-a6c","parent_id":"ready-24b","priority":"p2","title":"fix: TOFU non-interactive auto-pin silently accepts any beacon root in CI/agent context","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"9583fea7-e82b-4411-b61d-154bc3693946","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775664715625208742,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"context":"In cmd/rd/join.go + pkg/rdconfig/config.go, there is no file lock between Load() and Save(). Two concurrent 'rd join --root X' and 'rd join --root Y' processes can both read BeaconRoot='' simultaneously, both believe they are performing the first TOFU pin, and both write their respective roots — last writer wins silently. The expected behavior is that the second concurrent first-use should see a non-empty BeaconRoot and trigger the deviation guard. Fix: use file locking (e.g. flock or advisory lock on rd.json) around the Load-check-Save sequence in join, OR use an atomic compare-and-swap via OS-level rename semantics. Severity: minor in practice (concurrent rd join is rare) but is a logical integrity hole in the TOFU protocol.","for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-2dc","parent_id":"ready-24b","priority":"p2","title":"fix: TOCTOU race on TOFU beacon root pin — concurrent rd join can silently overwrite","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"b53e7905-09be-406b-9a0f-359a4abc7f10","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775664723964023477,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"context":"In pkg/state/state.go Derive(), when a cross-campfire ref appears as the BLOCKED item (p.BlockedID is cross-campfire, p.BlockerID is local), the code correctly attaches the warning to the local item (localItemID = p.BlockerID). However the warning message always uses p.BlockerID as the embedded ref string, not the actual cross-campfire ref (p.BlockedID). Result: the CrossCampfireWarning for this case says 'unresolved cross-campfire dep: \u003clocal-item-id\u003e ...' — which is a local ID, not a cross-campfire ref. When crossdep.ResolveDeps processes this warning, extractRef returns the local item ID, ParseCrossCampfireRef returns nil (no dots), and the dep is returned as unresolvable with the wrong ref. This produces confusing output and means this dep relationship is never resolvable even when the user is a member of the relevant campfire. Fix: use p.BlockedID in the warning format string when blockedIsCross=true. Severity: minor (incorrect warning/display, not a security vulnerability).","for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-129","parent_id":"ready-24b","priority":"p3","title":"fix: cross-campfire warning message uses wrong item ID when blockedIsCross=true","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"a8ba1401-b582-48b6-9292-b767b419fa6f","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775664731720188588,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"context":"In pkg/crossdep/crossdep.go resolveSingle(), when full alias lookup on 'acme.frontend' fails, the code retries with only the last segment 'frontend'. If the user has a short alias 'frontend' pointing to a different campfire than the one the cross-campfire ref author intended, the dep resolves against the wrong campfire. This means a crafted work:block message with 'evil.frontend.item-abc' will resolve against whatever campfire the user has aliased as 'frontend', not 'evil.frontend'. An attacker who can send messages to a shared campfire and knows the user's alias names can probe which aliases exist (an alias hit vs miss produces different display output). The fallback was added for usability but weakens the namespace isolation that the dot-separated campfire name path is meant to provide. Fix: remove the last-segment fallback, or at minimum add a warning when the fallback is used. Severity: major — breaks namespace isolation guarantees.","for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-134","parent_id":"ready-24b","priority":"p2","title":"fix: last-segment alias fallback in crossdep may resolve unintended campfire","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"e5631fc3-266f-4510-a288-8be7615632ff","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775664740183502586,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"context":"In cmd/rd/join.go, neither campfireID (args[0]) nor beaconRoot (--root flag) are validated before use. Both are stored directly to config and passed to client.Join(). While the current uses are comparison and truncated display (no injection risk), storing arbitrary strings as campfire IDs in the config creates risk for future code that might use them in paths or protocol operations. Recommended: validate that both values match the expected hex ID format (64 hex characters) before proceeding. Severity: minor — no exploitable injection currently, but hygiene issue.","for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-124","parent_id":"ready-24b","priority":"p3","title":"fix: no input validation on campfireID or beaconRoot in rd join","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"cd97510b-4b7f-4416-baa2-58ad497748a6","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775664747427832773,"operation":"work:close","payload":{"reason":"Reviewed Wave 4 commit 6a9a0f4. 0 critical, 3 major, 3 minor findings. Child items created: ready-f43 (pin-before-join ordering — major), ready-a6c (non-interactive TOFU auto-pin bypass — major), ready-134 (last-segment alias fallback breaks namespace isolation — major), ready-2dc (TOCTOU race on TOFU pin — minor), ready-2dc (TOCTOU — minor), ready-129 (wrong item ID in cross-campfire warning — minor), ready-124 (no input validation on join args — minor). No credential leaks, no auth bypass in membership check, no injection surfaces. BeaconRoot stored at 0600 permissions. Membership check in crossdep correctly gates on store membership. Config save uses 0600 permissions. Primary concerns are TOFU protocol integrity (pin-before-join, non-interactive auto-pin, TOCTOU) and alias namespace isolation (last-segment fallback).","resolution":"done","target":"68811c47-c37e-42c5-af96-5986a9babc46"},"tags":["work:close"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"9d2ebf4f-7984-4968-85f7-1fd3bf210c7f","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775664755052484542,"operation":"work:close","payload":{"reason":"Reviewed Wave 4 tests: all 6 done conditions covered, 100+ tests passing, ground-source testing confirmed. No critical or major findings. Minor gap: no integration test for rd show displaying cross-campfire deps (but code path verified by inspection).","resolution":"done","target":"5334af1c-83f2-4276-b16b-0b7f57d23414"},"tags":["work:close"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
