{"msg_id":"e4fb7eb0-85bd-4b3d-abf3-7ff3ee40861c","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775665118606691078,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-4b6","parent_id":"ready-d1a","priority":"p1","title":"BUG: buildDepTree deletes visited entry after processing, allowing infinite recursion in cycle","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"fb2698a8-24de-4cc1-8232-f0c11ed4fe3c","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775665121890029388,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-bd0","parent_id":"ready-d1a","priority":"p1","title":"BUG: validateNameFormat misses trailing /.. path traversal sequences","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"f214a918-d99f-4ce3-93da-f42264373d52","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775665121908492823,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-6ef","parent_id":"ready-d1a","priority":"p2","title":"BUG: grantMsgID and result.MessageID truncated at [:12] without length guard — panic if short","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"6595eadd-dfdc-447a-9fcc-79edc2909754","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775665127381679303,"operation":"work:close","payload":{"reason":"Duplicate — superseded by ready-f34 which has the correct title for the captoken IssueToken panic bug","resolution":"done","target":"382e6e41-f442-44c7-b23b-90c57ecd54bf"},"tags":["work:close"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"992b31c9-9ffc-4a87-9dba-6107c23327fc","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775665131566572225,"operation":"work:update","payload":{"context":"pkg/captoken/captoken.go:188 — IssueToken() accesses operations[0] at line 188 before the len(operations)==0 guard at line 189. If called with an empty slice, this panics with index out of range. The len guard must be checked first. Trigger: any caller passing an empty operations list to IssueToken(). This is a latent panic in the capability token issuance path.","target":"cff8c5a3-65cd-4d2f-8a98-141bc14c5795"},"tags":["work:update"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"2ebd457c-766c-4834-9383-94fd58d6e40d","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775665138683116849,"operation":"work:update","payload":{"context":"The serverBindingPayload struct is defined twice with incompatible field types: (1) conventionserver/server.go:410 — ValidFrom int64, ValidUntil int64 (writes JSON numbers). (2) state/state.go:206 — ValidFrom string, ValidUntil string (tries to unmarshal into strings). JSON numbers do NOT unmarshal into Go string fields — the field silently stays empty string. parseTimestamp('') returns 0. Result: findActiveServerBinding always returns nil because validFrom==0 causes every binding to be skipped as 'not yet valid'. This breaks isOperationAuthorized for ALL consequential operations (close, delegate, gate-resolve) in a campfire that has a server-binding declared — they are all rejected as unauthorized. Observable failure: work:close messages are silently dropped from derived state when a server-binding exists.","target":"04e67621-e737-41ea-808f-ae7c5361dd8a"},"tags":["work:update"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"2cc9a422-3d93-4585-9a2f-de3576affdf9","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775665150257921247,"operation":"work:update","payload":{"context":"cmd/rd/dep.go:264 — buildDepTree() sets visited[id]=true (line 248), processes children (recursively calling buildDepTree with same visited map), then calls delete(visited, id) at line 264. The delete is meant to allow the same node to appear in multiple branches (not truly a cycle). However, if there IS a genuine cycle (A blocks B, B blocks A), the delete means: when processing A we mark visited[A]=true, descend into B, descend back into A — A IS in visited so we return the cycle node. But after B finishes and we delete visited[B], if A appears again via a different path, we'd recurse again. In a true cycle A-\u003eB-\u003eA, the delete at the end of A's processing means if A is reached via a third path, visited[A] is gone and we recurse again — infinite recursion/stack overflow. Trigger: item with cyclic block edges (A blocks B, B blocks A) plus a third path to A.","target":"e4fb7eb0-85bd-4b3d-abf3-7ff3ee40861c"},"tags":["work:update"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"f22b9ba9-73b4-4030-938f-46b8f93e79ec","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775665156292243618,"operation":"work:close","payload":{"reason":"Dead code sweep complete: 32 unused items found (6 from staticcheck, 26 unreachable functions). All items identified as safe-to-delete. See item notes for full list.","resolution":"done","target":"33d9cf01-d8e1-4695-bf97-792d6cedae98"},"tags":["work:close"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"447d1eda-6cdf-4d59-b98f-62a5ac12ae6a","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775665156297168993,"operation":"work:update","payload":{"context":"cmd/rd/join.go:278 — validateNameFormat() checks for path traversal via strings.Contains(input, '../') and input=='..'. But it misses the trailing case: 'foo/..' passes validation because it doesn't contain '../' (no trailing slash) and is not exactly '..'. An attacker or buggy name resolution returning 'malicious/..' would pass the format check. The fix: also check strings.HasSuffix(input, '/..'). Severity: medium — defense in depth issue since the validated value is used as a campfire name argument, not a filesystem path directly. But validateNameFormat is designed as a security gate, and having a gap undermines its purpose.","target":"fb2698a8-24de-4cc1-8232-f0c11ed4fe3c"},"tags":["work:update"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"d7af7870-f334-4f30-8e5e-71f8d4731fe3","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775665162810123447,"operation":"work:update","payload":{"context":"cmd/rd/admit.go:222,233 and cmd/rd/revoke.go:78,117 — multiple sites truncate message IDs or pubkeys with [:12] without a length guard. In admit.go lines 222 and 233: grantMsgID[:12] is called on the message ID returned by admitThenGrant. If the executor returns an ID shorter than 12 chars (unusual but possible in test doubles, error paths, or future protocol changes), this panics. Same pattern in revoke.go:78 result.MessageID[:12] and line 117 r2.MessageID[:12]. The display-only truncations for displayKey are guarded by a prior length check, but the grantMsgID/result.MessageID truncations are not. Fix: use min(12, len(id)) or check len before slicing, consistent with the minInt helper already defined in send.go.","target":"f214a918-d99f-4ce3-93da-f42264373d52"},"tags":["work:update"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"5f165307-47c1-48bf-8693-1d6a22a59834","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775665164106611839,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-e11","parent_id":"ready-802","priority":"p1","title":"SEC: IssueToken panics on empty operations slice (out-of-bounds before nil check)","type":"bug"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"fb972ec2-2411-43f8-94f6-f027cf3611a0","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775665164911133398,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-34d","parent_id":"ready-802","priority":"p1","title":"SEC: revoke uses campfireID as pubkey when target is a name (semantic type confusion)","type":"bug"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"cf570602-f4f7-4128-8ea9-cd5fb8fe1979","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775665167072625532,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-7c3","parent_id":"ready-802","priority":"p1","title":"SEC: IsSoloMode does not check server-binding ValidUntil — stale binding blocks solo mode indefinitely","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"096d3b3e-3dfa-40b6-b1be-48f011b55bfb","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775665175424237131,"operation":"work:close","payload":{"reason":"Security sweep complete: 0 critical, 3 high, 4 medium, 1 low. High: (1) IssueToken panics on empty operations (captoken.go:188, operations[0] before len check) → ready-e11; (2) revoke resolves name to campfireID and uses it as pubkey in role-grant (revoke.go:45-49) → ready-34d; (3) IsSoloMode never checks ValidUntil on server-binding, stale binding blocks solo mode (server.go:448-468) → ready-7c3. Medium: (4) isHexString in inbox_watcher rejects uppercase hex, isHex in join.go accepts it — pubkey with uppercase chars passes admit but fails inbox; (5) requested_role field not validated before materializing to project campfire; (6) OptionalAttestations/OptionalJoinConversationCampfire have no length limits; (7) validateNameFormat misses trailing foo/.. pattern. Low: (8) authorizationMatrix defined but never enforced in makeHandler (design-correct for solo mode but misleading).","resolution":"done","target":"b7dab3e8-abc0-4ce3-9b9d-d03e153b4102"},"tags":["work:close"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"bf54a7c6-ff3d-4076-9a76-3c660c06eb1c","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775665182054619386,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-430","parent_id":"ready-d1a","priority":"p2","title":"BUG: role-grant granted_at sent as RFC3339 string but Derive() parses as int64 nanoseconds — field silently ignored","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"d47881ec-d71f-4d56-9e04-b9ba2d767a71","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775665188861857538,"operation":"work:update","payload":{"context":"cmd/rd/admit.go:274,278 and cmd/rd/revoke.go:63,68 — granted_at is built as RFC3339 string: now := time.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339). It is passed in the role-grant payload as a string. In state/state.go:473, Derive() parses role-grant messages into a struct with 'GrantedAt int64'. JSON unmarshal of a string value into int64 fails silently in Go — the field stays 0. So p.GrantedAt==0 always, and the code falls back to m.Timestamp (message arrival time). The grantedAt ordering comparison on line 488 ('grantedAt \u003e= existing.grantedAt') thus compares message timestamps, not the explicitly provided granted_at. This is always correct in practice (messages are replayed in order), but the granted_at field intended for migration/import purposes is completely non-functional. Fix: use int64 unix nanoseconds in the payload, or parse RFC3339 in the struct.","target":"bf54a7c6-ff3d-4076-9a76-3c660c06eb1c"},"tags":["work:update"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
