{"msg_id":"60901ad8-19de-439f-82c8-a544c05dfe29","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775665197052142321,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-f32","parent_id":"ready-d1a","priority":"p2","title":"BUG: isHexString in inbox_watcher rejects uppercase hex pubkeys — valid join requests silently dropped","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"d8a17c52-239f-407f-a59b-68b862f8ea7f","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775665207254025558,"operation":"work:update","payload":{"context":"pkg/conventionserver/inbox_watcher.go:217 — isHexString() only accepts lowercase hex [0-9a-f]. But join-request senders may encode their pubkey with uppercase hex [0-9A-F] (e.g., Go's encoding/hex produces lowercase, but other implementations may not). A valid 64-char pubkey with any uppercase character is rejected at line 121-123 with 'invalid pubkey format'. By contrast, isHex() in cmd/rd/join.go:410 accepts both cases. Fix: accept both cases in isHexString, or use strings.ToLower before validation.","target":"60901ad8-19de-439f-82c8-a544c05dfe29"},"tags":["work:update"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
