{"msg_id":"5783c9e4-3728-43d9-8892-35ec7a6550de","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775676253557468816,"operation":"work:block","payload":{"blocked_id":"ready-b63","blocked_msg":"f774f2db-f781-4301-9c84-19e8f6cd1927","blocker_id":"ready-7bb","blocker_msg":"0b350895-47c3-41e4-aa93-2f6370d8e145"},"tags":["work:block"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"90d6bea5-eb95-44af-9d62-f684af8f19d0","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775676253571910473,"operation":"work:update","payload":{"context":"## Bug\nrd join \u003ccampfire-id\u003e calls cf join (gets campfire membership) but creates no local project state. After rd join, the member's project directory has no .campfire/root, no .ready/config.json, no .ready/mutations.jsonl. Every rd command fails or returns empty.\n\n## Location\ncmd/rd/join.go — joinCmd.RunE. The join flow calls client.Join() and prints success but never calls rdconfig.Save() or creates .campfire/root.\n\n## Fix\nAfter successful cf join, rd join must:\n1. Create .campfire/root with the campfire ID\n2. Create .ready/config.json with campfire_id and sync config (mirror what rd init creates, minus campfire creation)\n3. Create empty .ready/mutations.jsonl\n4. Run initial rd sync pull to bootstrap local state from the campfire\n\n## Done condition\nAfter rd join \u003ccampfire-id\u003e, the member can immediately run rd sync pull and rd ready and see items created by the owner. Test: demo 07 hosted real-time script passes.","target":"154a927d-4f30-4b1c-8831-7f2fa1836da3"},"tags":["work:update"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"02032e9a-f72b-497f-b54d-c8301840988b","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775676253586379680,"operation":"work:update","payload":{"context":"## Bug\nConvention server authorization matrix requires operator provenance level 2 for work:close. Members admitted via rd admit get provenance level 1. Result: admitted members can create and claim items but cannot close them. The close operation buffers to pending.jsonl with error \"operator provenance level 1 insufficient: operation work:close requires level 2\".\n\n## Location\npkg/conventionserver/server.go — authorizationMatrix map. Also check how rd admit sets the member's operator level.\n\n## Investigation needed\n1. What provenance level does rd admit grant? Where is this set?\n2. Is level 2 intentional for close (security gate) or a misconfiguration?\n3. If intentional: rd admit needs a way to grant level 2, or close needs to accept level 1\n4. If misconfiguration: fix the authorization matrix\n\n## Done condition\nA member admitted via rd admit can run rd done \u003citem-id\u003e and have the close message reach the hosted campfire (not just buffer locally). Test: demo 07 member closes item, owner syncs and sees status=done.","target":"aa81e31c-13f8-4b8d-8428-94430ca76c5b"},"tags":["work:update"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"1bcb7920-b801-49eb-a6eb-c4f04c364ca7","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775676253601600473,"operation":"work:update","payload":{"context":"## Bug\nAfter owner creates an item on Machine A and member does rd sync pull on Machine B, only 1 message is pulled and the item doesn't appear in rd ready. The sync pull may be filtering by tags too aggressively, paginating incorrectly, or missing messages that are needed for state derivation.\n\n## Location\ncmd/rd/sync.go or pkg/sync/ — the pull implementation. Also check how state.Derive() processes the pulled messages.\n\n## Investigation needed\n1. How many messages does rd init + rd create actually produce? (declarations, create, etc.)\n2. Does sync pull filter by work:* tags? Does it miss convention:* messages needed for state?\n3. Is there a pagination issue (only pulling first page)?\n4. After pull, check .ready/mutations.jsonl — how many records? Does Derive() produce items from them?\n\n## Done condition\nAfter rd sync pull, all work:create messages from the campfire appear in the local mutations.jsonl, and rd ready shows the expected items. Test: demo 07 member sees owner's item after sync pull.","target":"f774f2db-f781-4301-9c84-19e8f6cd1927"},"tags":["work:update"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
