{"msg_id":"9ac917fe-c31c-4741-9d91-94c14e4242ac","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775692163046166881,"operation":"work:claim","payload":{"target":"7fe8f403-5ec4-492f-9427-216ea06252aa"},"tags":["work:claim"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"786c18e8-a237-4f23-98c5-ce0dfd41d5a2","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775692181137252196,"operation":"work:claim","payload":{"target":"bfc8aa7f-0b1b-4832-8ca8-f1885f6e93fd"},"tags":["work:claim"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"21bcea90-bde0-4a80-8008-6353d1f74437","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775692190310579202,"operation":"work:close","payload":{"reason":"Security sweep complete. 3 findings: (1) invite token encodes private key seed in base64url JSON with no integrity/HMAC — token tampering undetected (informational, no current exploit path); (2) IsSoloMode uses Unix seconds for ValidUntil comparison but ValidUntil is stored as UnixNano — 1-hour bindings never expire in solo mode detection, stale bindings not evicted; (3) cross-campfire dep prefix resolution in resolveAcrossCampfires and findItemInCampfire uses HasPrefix which could allow a crafted item ID to match unintended targets across campfires. No critical auth bypass found.","resolution":"done","target":"a0136778-d253-42a0-9ee3-f638f8112344"},"tags":["work:close"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"73c86edb-e810-406d-ab49-d5fd0c667d9a","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775692194809962309,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-d81","parent_id":"ready-3d6","priority":"p1","title":"Security fix: IsSoloMode compares ValidUntil nanoseconds against Unix seconds — stale server bindings never expire","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"f18cd802-64bb-4cff-a1a5-8df8d990342d","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775692205671244907,"operation":"work:update","payload":{"context":"IsSoloMode (server.go line 465) compares ValidUntil against time.Now().Unix() (seconds), but ValidUntil is stored as UnixNano (line 394: now.Add(time.Hour).UnixNano()). UnixNano values (~1.7e18) always exceed Unix seconds (~1.7e9), so stale bindings from old rd processes are never treated as expired. A stale binding causes IsSoloMode to return false (remote server present), so the in-process solo server is not started. Subsequent rd commands have no server to fulfill them and silently fail or drop mutations. Fix: use time.Now().UnixNano() in the IsSoloMode comparison, or change ensureServerBinding to store ValidUntil as Unix seconds.","target":"73c86edb-e810-406d-ab49-d5fd0c667d9a"},"tags":["work:update"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"e9b70780-5df2-4486-89c1-208c481596af","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775692221714958401,"operation":"work:update","payload":{"context":"Security audit of the rd invite / rd join token flow confirms no auth bypass, key leakage, or TOCTOU vulnerabilities.\n\n## Security Review Findings\n\n### Finding 1: Token reuse not prevented (MEDIUM)\nToken described as one-use but nothing enforces single-use. Within TTL window, token is freely replayable. Intercepted token grants persistent campfire access.\n\n### Finding 2: No audit trail for invite issuance (LOW)\nrd invite posts no campfire message recording that an invite was issued. No server-side record of when/by whom/for what purpose.\n\n### Finding 3: Identity overwrite with --force has no confirmation (LOW)\njoinViaInviteToken with --force overwrites existing identity without confirmation or backup — destructive, social-engineering risk.\n\n### Finding 4: TTL is client-side only (MEDIUM)\nToken expiry checked only in decodeInviteToken() client-side. The pubkey is already admitted server-side regardless of TTL. Expired tokens still contain valid credentials extractable by bypassing the CLI.\n\n### Finding 7: Token not encrypted or signed (INFO)\nToken is base64url JSON, no encryption/MAC. Acceptable given treat-as-secret model but means tokens MUST use secure channels.\n\n### Not Vulnerable\n- TOCTOU: No race window — keypair generated fresh, pubkey admitted atomically before token printed\n- Key scoping: Identity admitted to exactly one campfire, correct\n- Test coverage: Solid for decode path (7 test cases)","target":"e7615dd8-fe00-4bfb-b596-350c7d11527c"},"tags":["work:update"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"d4156488-630c-4364-aaf9-98254e383406","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775692225339335225,"operation":"work:close","payload":{"reason":"Test coverage sweep complete. 3 gaps found: (1) clientLister in sync.go has zero direct unit tests — only exercised via E2E join auto-sync test; the timestamp-filter branch (afterTimestamp \u003e 0) and multi-filter-tag extraction branch are untested in isolation; (2) validateBeaconRootTOFU non-interactive first-use path (the path that returns an error in non-interactive mode) is tested via TestValidateBeaconRoot_FirstUse_NonInteractiveRequiresConfirm in join_test.go but the new TOFU-defer split means applyBeaconRootTOFU (deprecated) and validateBeaconRootTOFU are both present — the integration path where validateBeaconRootTOFU blocks and join aborts (no pin saved) is not unit-tested without a full join; (3) joinViaInviteToken force-overwrite path (--force flag, identity already exists) has no unit test — only the happy path and error-on-existing-identity are exercised in the E2E tests. All other paths have adequate coverage.","resolution":"done","target":"7fe8f403-5ec4-492f-9427-216ea06252aa"},"tags":["work:close"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"2cd0ddba-b635-43d1-8512-259fe067846e","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775692225631652868,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-0f6","priority":"p1","title":"Security fix: enforce single-use invite tokens","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"89b64f72-aa9d-4469-8a90-7a262523a5b5","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775692225936019123,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-1fc","priority":"p1","title":"Security fix: server-side TTL enforcement for invite tokens","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"acf6fb1d-8db0-44dd-b143-f63d372605b6","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775692231525691306,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-c0e","parent_id":"ready-3d6","priority":"p2","title":"Test: clientLister timestamp-filter and tag-extraction branches in sync.go","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"74d07884-9509-4374-b4c6-6a99ee808a05","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775692231541576708,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-328","parent_id":"ready-3d6","priority":"p2","title":"Test: joinViaInviteToken --force overwrite path (identity already exists)","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"1f799fa8-26a7-4ef4-853b-90f8cbd989ca","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775692234660271640,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-c49","parent_id":"ready-3d6","priority":"p1","title":"Bug fix: IsSoloMode uses Unix() to compare ValidUntil stored as UnixNano() — expiry check never fires","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"a50ba9f6-2c5b-4bf2-bb17-8471118d790a","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775692235357910422,"operation":"work:update","payload":{"context":"Token described as one-use (invite.go:33) but nothing enforces it. Within TTL window, intercepted token is freely replayable — multiple parties can join with the same identity.\n\nFix options:\n(a) Server-side: track redeemed pubkeys, reject re-join with same pre-provisioned key after first use\n(b) Post audit message on first join so issuer can detect duplicate use\n(c) At minimum: rd join should post a campfire message when an invite token identity first joins, creating a detectable trail\n\nFiles: cmd/rd/invite.go, cmd/rd/join.go (joinViaInviteToken)","target":"2cd0ddba-b635-43d1-8512-259fe067846e"},"tags":["work:update"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"06bc5e55-de61-45f2-bb77-4572a0c87d6a","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775692235374581905,"operation":"work:update","payload":{"context":"Token expiry is checked only client-side in decodeInviteToken() (invite.go:158). The pubkey is admitted to the campfire at invite time — it remains admitted indefinitely regardless of TTL. An attacker who extracts the private key seed from an expired token can construct a protocol client directly, bypassing the CLI expiry check.\n\nFix: after TTL expires, the issuer (or automated cleanup) should revoke the admitted pubkey if no join occurred. This requires tracking issuance (see ready-0f6). Alternative: add a reaper that scans for admitted-but-never-joined keys older than TTL and revokes them.\n\nFiles: cmd/rd/invite.go, cmd/rd/join.go, cmd/rd/revoke.go","target":"89b64f72-aa9d-4469-8a90-7a262523a5b5"},"tags":["work:update"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"88f8ca66-323b-47ec-b03d-45679a6bc72c","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775692237106567515,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"for":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd","id":"ready-f3c","parent_id":"ready-3d6","priority":"p1","title":"Bug fix: joinViaInviteToken overwrites identity before join succeeds — no rollback on join failure","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"8c7dc9b4-a0d9-4dcd-87d6-f2b64ef623a8","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775692239362163790,"operation":"work:close","payload":{"reason":"Security review complete. 2 MEDIUM findings (token reuse: ready-0f6, client-side-only TTL: ready-1fc), 2 LOW findings (no audit trail, --force overwrite without confirmation), 1 INFO (token not encrypted). No auth bypass, no TOCTOU, key scoping correct.","resolution":"done","target":"e7615dd8-fe00-4bfb-b596-350c7d11527c"},"tags":["work:close"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"924174e0-f41a-4022-9472-7eb0e1534c7c","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775692248793715153,"operation":"work:update","payload":{"context":"In pkg/conventionserver/server.go: ensureServerBinding stores ValidUntil as time.Now().Add(time.Hour).UnixNano() (nanoseconds, ~1.7e18), but IsSoloMode compares it against time.Now().Unix() (seconds, ~1.7e9). Since ValidUntil (~1e18) is always greater than now in seconds (~1e9), the expiry condition b.ValidUntil \u003c now never fires. Stale server bindings from crashed/stopped remote servers persist forever, permanently blocking solo mode detection. Fix: use UnixNano() consistently in IsSoloMode (change line 458 to now := time.Now().UnixNano()).","target":"1f799fa8-26a7-4ef4-853b-90f8cbd989ca"},"tags":["work:update"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"3e576224-f0d7-40e2-a6ce-7a7df4f588de","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775692248810226076,"operation":"work:update","payload":{"context":"In cmd/rd/join.go joinViaInviteToken: identity is written to disk (id.Save ~line 617) and protocolClient is reset to nil BEFORE client.Join() is called. If Join() fails, the old identity is destroyed with no recovery path. The user is left broken: original identity gone, new identity cannot join. Fix: backup old identity bytes before overwriting (or write to a temp path and rename only on successful join).","target":"88f8ca66-323b-47ec-b03d-45679a6bc72c"},"tags":["work:update"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"79b30c32-9bf6-4dc5-990d-9b9633789dba","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775692254626840004,"operation":"work:close","payload":{"reason":"Bug sweep complete. 2 confirmed bugs found: (1) ready-c49: IsSoloMode in pkg/conventionserver/server.go compares ValidUntil (stored as UnixNano) against time.Now().Unix() (seconds) — expiry check never fires, stale remote server bindings persist forever. (2) ready-f3c: joinViaInviteToken in cmd/rd/join.go writes and activates new identity before client.Join() succeeds — no rollback on join failure destroys the previous identity. No bugs found in: invite token decode/validation, auto-sync pull (clientLister), cross-campfire dep resolution (crossdep.go), dep add/remove logic, create pipe-friendly output, init durability skip, or root.go inbox skip.","resolution":"done","target":"683568a6-b478-433b-a448-1ae8e1c95a8b"},"tags":["work:close"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
{"msg_id":"1bd18620-dc6a-4cd5-80c7-a33b6df17e83","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775692981391323809,"operation":"work:close","payload":{"reason":"All 10 demos rebuilt with ergonomic sugar: rd invite token flow (ready-c31), direct rd create capture (ready-e09), no --confirm on rd init (ready-b56), auto-sync on join (ready-5cd), real cross-project dep wiring in demo 03 (ready-cc0). All demos verified passing. site/index.html updated. PR: https://github.com/campfire-net/ready/pull/47","resolution":"done","target":"bfc8aa7f-0b1b-4832-8ca8-f1885f6e93fd"},"tags":["work:close"],"sender":"1e224c14bc7959bf6bec7d4e563389b6c3d3e9255ad206df1ba60cdc52197ffd"}
